 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search HR Digital Integration Architect Facebook 631 reviews Austin, TX Facebook 631 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. The Global People Operations team within Facebook strives to create and deliver a seamless and positive experience across an employee's lifecycle. Our focus is to develop an efficient and straightforward HR ecosystem. We support people-related strategies across the organization through accurate people data management, business capabilities, and project management. We strive to ensure employees feel heard and are provided the resources and support they need during the most important moments during their careers. As we evolve into an era of unparalleled speed and scale where innovation is faster, we derive more insights from data, and digital interaction is delivered in real-time, we also need to expand roles to support this environment. This includes leading a business strategy that focuses on digital integration, defining HR architecture, and identifying system impacts. The digital integration architect will be the primary role to lead the effort in aiding the business to establish integration strategies, which span end to end across the domain, creating a diverse, efficient HR environment. This role will need to be proficient and knowledgeable in the digital landscape of integration from business and technical perspectives.
 Lead End-to-End international employee Intranet design from strategy to execution, collaborating with a global team embedding business adoption of internal digital workplace platforms and federating multiple local intranets 
Provide expert-level advice and knowledge for establishing a smart international content strategy integrating a digital ecosystem transformation, understanding intranet, social, search, digital assistants, mobile app channels, etc. to be synthesized from multiple platforms for a positive digital employee experience 
Serve as primary business and IT Liaison with HR business and tech teams on complex integration issues, and supports the development of technical, operational, and functional requirements as well as the required interface agreements and MOUs 
Document as is and collaboratively define future state digital ecosystems for HR integration business solutions, enable digital integration roadmaps, and analyze business needs 
Implement best practices for security and data integrity and interoperability 
Partner with cross functional teams to establish change management activities, plan resource alignment, identify priority adjustments, and identify needed skill sets 
Analyzes and documents users’ functional and data requirements to help determine technical requirements and architectural design options for specific HR domains 
Document and define intelligent automation journeys to streamline workflows, determine data requirements for both internal and external interfaces 
10+ years of combined experience as an Integration Architect, Engineer, Solutions Architect, Technical Consultant, or Partner/Sales Engineer 
3+ years as technical lead for MuleSoft and API Management integration projects 
2 years of full MuleSoft development life cycle project experience and providing architecture analysis, build and test MuleSoft integrations 
2+ years of experience working with software systems including product development, software engineering, and working with API development or troubleshooting 
Experience communicating with technical and business audience at prospects or clients 
Experience with web, mobile, or enterprise technology stack 
Experience demonstrating knowledge of industry integration technology areas and trends 
Understanding API specifications and troubleshooting scripting experience 
Understanding of all the stages of API and Experience with one or more programming languages for API development 
Experience and willingness to quickly learn new technologies tool and training 
Leadership experience in architecting, developing and deploying enterprise class solutions in customer facing environments 
Experience driving business solutions and strategies to connect multiple HR domains across the enterprise (global) 
Proficient in advising management and tech teams, inside and outside own organization, on system architecture, technical results, or risks 
Knowledge about API design standards, patterns and best-practices. Hands-on experience in API management platforms and API related activities: requirement analysis, solution architecture and design, resource-based API modelling, micro-services architecture 
Experience in Salesforce Service Cloud and MuleSoft integration platform 
Experience Integrating solutions using Cloud-based technologies, structured and unstructured Big Data, and Automation, Augmentation and Artificial Intelligence technologies 
Understanding of Platforms integration mobile, web, portal, and related technologies 
Experience with understanding of systems engineering lifecycle 
Experience in promoting quality control practices through continuous integration and continuous deployment efforts and assist with activities necessary to remain compliant and ensure security requirements are met 
Experience with systems integration and test, system verification and validation, and systems engineering 
B.S. or M.S. in Technical Discipline (Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics) or equivalent experience 
Experience deploying large-scale integration projects 
Agile-based knowledge and skills 
